<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-02-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-02-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="123" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d123">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 841.857/332</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-02-10">
                                        <hi rend="italic">February 10, 1917</hi></date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 12.15 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>5658. My 5685, 8th.<note n="3" xml:id="d123fn3">Not printed.</note>
                                Affidavits of captain, first and second mates, and American
                                master-at-arms of <hi rend="italic">California</hi>, which Consul,
                                Queens-town is forwarding to you, give no information beyond what
                                already telegraphed but reiterates ship torpedoed without any sort
                                of warning and that loss of life due to rapidity with which ship
                                sank.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_PWH1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Page</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>